Preheat your #oven{} (for the tortillas) to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve, peel and chop the @onion{1} into small pieces.

Cut the @tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.

Cut the @mushrooms{250%grams} into slices.

> TIP: If you want to avoid turning on your oven you can dry-fry the tortillas in a pan instead.

Place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a drizzle of @oil{to taste}.

Once hot, fry the mushrooms, half the @Mexican Style Spice Mix{1%sachet} and half the onion until golden brown, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}.

Add the chickpeas, lightly crush with a #fork{} and cook until warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @coriander{5%grams}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all).

To make your salsa, mix together the tomato, remaining onion, and half the coriander in a #bowl{}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Quarter the @lime{1}.

Mix the @creme fraiche{125%grams}, remaining Mexican spice mix, and the juice of half a lime (double for 4p) together in a #small bowl{}.

Season to taste with salt and pepper.

Pop the @tortilla{8} into the oven to warm, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once warmed, divide between plates.

Serve the charred veg, tomato salsa, spiced creme fraiche, remaining coriander, @Grated Cheese{50%grams} and remaining lime wedges in separate bowls.

Allow everyone to top their veggie fajitas at the table.